cui_name: Advanced Lung Non-Squamous Non-Small Cell Carcinoma
reasoning: Specific subtype of lung cancer: NSCLC (~80% of lung cancer) × non-squamous histology (~60% of NSCLC) × advanced stage (III-IV, ~40-50% at diagnosis). Global lung cancer incidence ~25 per 100k; advanced non-squamous NSCLC estimated ~6.5 per 100k based on GLOBOCAN and cancer registry data.
source: GLOBOCAN 2020 (International Agency for Research on Cancer)
